title: Bodycam Footage - Ohio

communications.subject: Ohio Open Records Law Request: Bodycam Footage - Ohio
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Ohio Open Records Law, I hereby request the following records:

I am requesting copies of all body-worn camera footage, cruiser dash cam footage, and any other audio or video recordings related to the incident involving Marissa Bill that occurred on or around August 17, 2024, at Froggy’s at the Lake (also known as Froggy's Bar) in Bellefontaine, Ohio. If multiple deputies responded, I request body cam footage from each involved deputy.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 10 business days.

Sincerely,

Tavin Way

title: “Responsible Party” Designations and COVID‑19 Plan Communications (School Year 2021‑22)

communications.subject: New York Freedom of Information Law Request: “Responsible Party” Designations and COVID‑19 Plan Communications (School Year 2021‑22)
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the New York Freedom of Information Law, I hereby request the following records:

Pursuant to New York Public Officers Law §84 et seq. (FOIL), I hereby submit this as a brand new request for the following records held by the Niskayuna Central School District. This request supersedes and clarifies the February 7, 2022, request (MuckRock #124465-34497783; link: https://www.muckrock.com/foi/niskayuna-23437/foil-responsible-party-identification-and-communications-niskayuna-central-school-district-124465/), which was denied on March 25, 2022, for no responsive records. A timely appeal was filed March 31, 2022, under 21 NYCRR 1401.7(d), but the District's July 15, 2022, response addressed a later purported appeal and deemed it waived without acknowledging the initial filing or merits, raising concerns about timeline tracking and search adequacy.

The requested records are:

“RESPONSIBLE PARTY” DESIGNATIONS
• All documents, plans, submissions, or records where the designation of “Responsible Parties” is attested or identified under the NYS Department of Health document Interim Guidance for In‑Person Instruction at Pre‑K–12 Schools During the COVID‑19 Public Health Emergency (7 June 2021) for School Year 2021‑2022 (1 July 2021 – 30 June 2022), including any related attestations, affirmations, or sections of reopening plans that specify their roles, responsibilities, or identities.
• Any bonding or insurance certificates held specifically for those individuals in that capacity.

COVID‑19 REOPENING / IN‑PERSON INSTRUCTION PLANS
• All versions (initial submission, amendments, updates) of the District’s COVID‑19 reopening or in‑person instruction plan filed with NYSDOH or NYSED between 1 July 2021 and 30 June 2022, including cover letters or transmittal e‑mails.

AFFIRMATIONS OF COMPLIANCE
• Every written affirmation or certification sent to NYSDOH, NYSED, or the Schenectady County Department of Health in which a District official attested that the District would adhere to—or had read and understood—the above‑referenced DOH guidance during the same period.

EXTERNAL E‑MAIL CORRESPONDENCE ABOUT THE PLAN
Search only these District accounts: Superintendent, Director of Business & Finance, District Clerk, and any individual identified in the documents responsive to Item 1.
Time frame: 1 July 2021 – 30 June 2022
Keywords (Boolean OR): “COVID” “Responsible Party” “reopening plan” “Core Health” “containment” “closure” “monitoring”
Produce incoming and outgoing e‑mails (with attachments) exchanged with:
• @health.ny.gov (NY Department of Health)
• @nysed.gov (NY State Education Department)
• @schenectadycounty.com (or equivalent) (Schenectady County DOH)


Given prior delays—where no response to the initial appeal occurred within 10 business days under §89(4)(a), creating a constructive denial—and similar patterns in other requests (per COOG AOs like FOIL-AO-14913 and FOIL-AO-14159 on constructive denials from non-response or unauthorized extensions), I request immediate acknowledgment and determination. This is supported by cases such as Matter of Jewish Press, Inc. v. New York City Dept. of Corr. (183 A.D.3d 731 [2d Dept. 2021]) and Matter of Save Monroe Ave., Inc. v. New York State Dept. of Transp. (197 A.D.3d 808 [3d Dept. 2021]), emphasizing that inaction undermines openness, and COOG AO-19372 on delays from ignored appeals.

To avoid loss, preserve all responsive records per COOG AO-16073 (retention until resolution) and before LGS-01 timelines expire (e.g., 1 year for correspondence, 6 years for policy records), confirming in acknowledgment.

Provide records electronically (PDF for documents; .eml/.msg for e-mail) to minimize costs; I certify non-commercial use. For denials/redactions, release segregable portions with exemption log citing §87(2) subdivision and appeal rights. Acknowledge within 5 business days and respond or extend (with date-certain) within 20, per §89(3)(a).

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 5 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Jackson Parker

title: Records Generated and Retained

communications.subject: Freedom of Information Act Request: Records Generated and Retained
communications.communication:
To whom it may concern,

Pursuant to the Freedom of Information Act, I hereby request the following records:

Any and all materials, indices, directives, manuals, and other guiding documentation regarding the records generated and retained by this agency, including but not limited to any and all applicable:

• Record retention schedules
• Indices to the records management program
• Any other data structures used for the management of records: digital, paper, and otherwise

The category for this request is Media. I am a journalist with work that has appeared in The Narwhal, Slate, Sierra, and other publications, and I am requesting this information in that capacity.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by email attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 20 business days, as the statute requires. Please provide a tracking number and an estimated date of completion for the records.

Sincerely,

Elyse Hauser

title: SOR and Community Supervision

communications.subject: Iowa Open Records Law Request: SOR and Community Supervision
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Iowa Open Records Law, I hereby request the following records:

I am seeking data to understand offenders who have double forms of community supervision (i.e. parole and sex offender registry (SOR)). Iowa Department of Corrections had helped to provide a list of all offenders on probation and parole. I would like to be able to cross reference that list with the current Iowa SOR to pull the data I am seeking. I would like to request that the Division provide the list of offenders on the SOR currently. 

If that request is not possible, I wonder if the Division has: the exact number of people who are 1) on both the sex offender registry and probation; and 2) on both the sex offender registry and parole; as per the latest available data is requested.

If another agency has this data, I request the name of that agency.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 10 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Wendy Sawyer

title: Police disciplinary files (Island County Prosecuting Attorney)

communications.subject: Washington Public Records Act Request: Police disciplinary files (Island County Prosecuting Attorney)
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Washington Public Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

- Any and all lists, spreadsheets or other organized datasets that detail potential or substantiated allegations of misconduct and/or impeached or impeachable testimony, created under Brady v. Maryland and/or Giglio v. United States.
- Any and all records regarding substantiated allegations of misconduct or violations of internal department policy or criminal law by specific law enforcement officers.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 5 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Aspen Ford
